OL,3,CWelfare U-turn leaves a humiliated
OL,4,Cgovernment with a financial blackhole
OL,6,FEconomics Editor Joel Hills breaks
OL,7,Fdown the financial repercussions of
OL,8,Fthe government's welfare U-turn
OL,10,FThe welfare bill U-turn is politically
OL,11,Fembarrassing for the government, and
OL,12,Fit also leaves the chancellor with a
OL,13,Fsignificant financial problem.
OL,15,FIf you recall, the original plan was
OL,16,Frushed out before the Spring Statement
OL,17,Fin March because Rachel Reeves was in
OL,18,Fdanger of breaking the borrowing and
OL,19,Fdebt rules she had just set, at the
OL,20,Ffirst time of asking.
